---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
const lastUpdated = "January 18, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Use - Dome"
  description="Terms and conditions for use of Dome"
>
  <main class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to home</a>

      <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="last-updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <section>
        <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By downloading, installing, or using Dome ("the Application"), you
          accept these terms of use. If you do not agree with these terms, do
          not use the Application.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Description of the Service</h2>
        <p>
          Dome is an open-source desktop application for knowledge management
          and academic research. The Application works entirely offline and
          stores all data locally on your device.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. License to Use</h2>
        <p>
          Dome is distributed under the <strong>MIT License</strong>. This
          means you may:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use the Application for any purpose</li>
          <li>Modify the source code</li>
          <li>Distribute copies of the software</li>
          <li>Include the software in commercial projects</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          <strong>Attribution Requirement:</strong> You must include the
          original copyright notice and this license in all copies or
          substantial portions of the software.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Use of Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          The Application may optionally connect to third-party services for
          AI features:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>OpenAI:</strong> For embeddings and chat (GPT)</li>
          <li><strong>Anthropic:</strong> For chat (Claude)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Use of these services is subject to their own terms and privacy
          policies. API keys you provide are stored locally on your device.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          Content you create using Dome (notes, annotations, etc.) is your
          property. Dome’s source code is available under the MIT license with
          due credit to the original author.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          THE APPLICATION IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND. IN
          NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY
          CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER LIABILITY.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Contributions</h2>
        <p>
          If you contribute to the project, you agree that your contributions
          will be licensed under the same MIT terms and that the original
          author retains attribution rights over the project.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Changes to the Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Changes will
          be posted on this page with a new update date.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For questions about these terms, you may open an issue on the <a
            href="https://github.com/maxprain12/dome"
            target="_blank">GitHub repository</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding: 6rem 0 4rem;
    min-height: calc(100vh - 300px);
  }
  .container {
    max-width: 800px;
  }
  .back-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    transition: opacity var(--transition-fast);
  }
  .back-link:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .last-updated {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  ul {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  a {
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
